  <h2>Technical skills</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Programming and analysis:</strong> Python, R, Unix/shell scripting.
    <br />
    <strong>Workflow and infrastructure:</strong> Snakemake, Git, Conda, HPC, GPU computing.
    <br />
    <strong>Transcriptomics:</strong> bulk RNA-seq, single-cell RNA-seq, total-RNA sequencing,
    alternative splicing analysis, microexon discovery, PSI quantification.
    <br />
    <strong>Machine learning:</strong> supervised models, sequence-based splicing models, model
    interpretation, variant effect prediction.
    <br />
    <strong>Genomics:</strong> rare variant analysis, family-based autism genetics, regulatory
    variant interpretation.
  </p>

  <h2>Mentoring and collaboration</h2>
  <p>
    I have contributed to the development and mentorship of collaborative computational projects,
    including work with Hyunbeen "Jason" Lee on Alu-mediated RNA duplexes and exon skipping
    in primate transcriptomes (<em>Genome Biology</em>, 2026, co-first and co-corresponding author).
    Earlier mentorship includes work with Yuyao Song on alternative splicing in single-cell RNA-seq,
    culminating in a <em>Genome Biology</em> publication (scASfind, 2024).
  </p>

  <h2>Teaching and training</h2>
  <p>
    I have taught on the Wellcome Genome Campus Advanced Course on Next Generation Sequencing
    Bioinformatics in Chile (2019, 2021) and on University of Cambridge courses in RNA-seq
    analysis, Python programming, data science in Python, and computational methods for biological
    data analysis (2017–2019).
  </p>

